n\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/Defs.html#Module\">Module</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">E</span> → <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_extends\">extends</span> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/LinearMap/Defs.html#IsLinearMap\">IsLinearMap</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">f</span></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A function `f` satisfies `IsBoundedLinearMap 𝕜 f` if it is linear and satisfies the\ninequality `‖f x‖ ≤ M * ‖x‖` for some positive constant `M`.\n\n(We put only the typeclasses strictly necessary for the definition, although the main case of\ninterest is when `𝕜` itself is a normed ring and `E, F` are normed modules.) ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Operator/BoundedLinearMaps.html#IsBoundedLinearMap","kind":"structure","line":74,"name":"IsBoundedLinearMap","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Operator/BoundedLinearMaps.lean#L74-L81"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Analysis.Normed.Module.Multilinear.Basic","Mathlib.Analysis.Normed.Ring.Units","Mathlib.Analysis.Normed.Operator.Mul"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.Analysis.Normed.Operator.BoundedLinearMaps"}